{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0158QGp6bQrqGrVHyEs4QEUZ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# LLM_COMPAT Contract Spec (Rust)\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Objective\n4\t\n5\tDefine a production-grade Rust contract for provider-agnostic LLM communication.\n6\tThe agent must be able to call Anthropic Messages API and OpenAI Chat Completions API through\n7\ta single unified interface, with no provider-specific types leaking into upper layers.\n8\t\n9\t## 2. Evidence from Current Code\n10\t\n11\t1. `crates/llm-compat/src/request.rs`: `AnthropicRequest`, `OpenAiRequest` wire types.\n12\t2. `crates/llm-compat/src/response.rs`: `AnthropicResponse`, `OpenAiResponse`, streaming chunk types.\n13\t3. `crates/llm-compat/src/convert.rs`: bidirectional conversion functions (Anthropic <-> OpenAI).\n14\t4. `crates/llm-compat/tests/conversion.rs`: round-trip conversion tests.\n15\t\n16\tCurrent state: direct Anthropic <-> OpenAI conversion without a Canonical intermediate layer.\n17\t\n18\t## 3. Rust Ownership Boundaries\n19\t\n20\t### Crate mapping\n21\t\n22\t1. `crates/api-types`\n23\t   Purpose: define Canonical (provider-agnostic) message, tool_use, and streaming types.\n24\t\n25\t2. `crates/llm-compat`\n26\t   Purpose: convert between Canonical types and provider wire formats. House HTTP client traits and streaming adapters.\n27\t\n28\t3. `crates/config`\n29\t   Purpose: provider selection, API keys, model aliases, endpoint URLs, retry/timeout policies.\n30\t\n31\t4. `crates/app-services`\n32\t   Purpose: agent loop operates exclusively on Canonical types. Calls `LlmClient` trait (defined in `llm-compat`, parameterized by Canonical types from `api-types`).\n33\t\n34\t### Architectural rule\n35\t\n36\t```\n37\tapi-types (Canonical types)\n38\t    ↓\n39\tllm-compat (conversion + client trait + provider impls)\n40\t    ↓                          ↑\n41\tapp-services (agent loop)    config (provider selection)\n42\t```\n43\t\n44\t`app-services` depends on `llm-compat` via trait only.\n45\t`llm-compat` depends on `api-types` only.\n46\tNo provider wire types may appear in `app-services` or above.\n47\t\n48\t## 4. Core Contracts (Rust)\n49\t\n50\t### 4.1 Canonical Types (`crates/api-types/src/llm.rs`)\n51\t\n52\t```rust\n53\tuse serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};\n54\t\n55\t/// Provider-agnostic content block\n56\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq)]\n57\t#[serde(tag = \"type\")]\n58\tpub enum ContentBlock {\n59\t    #[serde(rename = \"text\")]\n60\t    Text { text: String },\n61\t    #[serde(rename = \"tool_use\")]\n62\t    ToolUse {\n63\t        id: String,\n64\t        name: String,\n65\t        input: serde_json::Value,\n66\t    },\n67\t    #[serde(rename = \"tool_result\")]\n68\t    ToolResult {\n69\t        tool_use_id: String,\n70\t        content: String,\n71\t        is_error: bool,\n72\t    },\n73\t    #[serde(rename = \"thinking\")]\n74\t    Thinking { thinking: String },\n75\t}\n76\t\n77\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq, Eq)]\n78\t#[serde(rename_all = \"snake_case\")]\n79\tpub enum Role {\n80\t    User,\n81\t    Assistant,\n82\t}\n83\t\n84\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq)]\n85\tpub struct Message {\n86\t    pub role: Role,\n87\t    pub content: Vec<ContentBlock>,\n88\t}\n89\t\n90\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq)]\n91\tpub struct ToolDefinition {\n92\t    pub name: String,\n93\t    pub description: String,\n94\t    pub input_schema: serde_json::Value,\n95\t}\n96\t\n97\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n98\tpub struct LlmRequest {\n99\t    pub model: String,\n100\t    pub system: Option<String>,\n101\t    pub messages: Vec<Message>,\n102\t    pub tools: Vec<ToolDefinition>,\n103\t    pub max_tokens: u32,\n104\t    pub temperature: Option<f32>,\n105\t    pub stream: bool,\n106\t}\n107\t\n108\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq, Eq)]\n109\t#[serde(rename_all = \"snake_case\")]\n110\tpub enum StopReason {\n111\t    EndTurn,\n112\t    ToolUse,\n113\t    MaxTokens,\n114\t    StopSequence,\n115\t}\n116\t\n117\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n118\tpub struct LlmResponse {\n119\t    pub id: String,\n120\t    pub model: String,\n121\t    pub content: Vec<ContentBlock>,\n122\t    pub stop_reason: Option<StopReason>,\n123\t    pub usage: TokenUsage,\n124\t}\n125\t\n126\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Serialize, Deserialize, Default)]\n127\tpub struct TokenUsage {\n128\t    pub input_tokens: u32,\n129\t    pub output_tokens: u32,\n130\t}\n131\t\n132\t/// Streaming event (provider-agnostic)\n133\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n134\t#[serde(tag = \"type\")]\n135\tpub enum StreamEvent {\n136\t    #[serde(rename = \"content_block_start\")]\n137\t    ContentBlockStart { index: usize, block: ContentBlock },\n138\t    #[serde(rename = \"content_block_delta\")]\n139\t    ContentBlockDelta { index: usize, delta: DeltaBlock },\n140\t    #[serde(rename = \"content_block_stop\")]\n141\t    ContentBlockStop { index: usize },\n142\t    #[serde(rename = \"message_stop\")]\n143\t    MessageStop {\n144\t        stop_reason: Option<StopReason>,\n145\t        usage: TokenUsage,\n146\t    },\n147\t}\n148\t\n149\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n150\t#[serde(tag = \"type\")]\n151\tpub enum DeltaBlock {\n152\t    #[serde(rename = \"text_delta\")]\n153\t    TextDelta { text: String },\n154\t    #[serde(rename = \"input_json_delta\")]\n155\t    InputJsonDelta { partial_json: String },\n156\t    #[serde(rename = \"thinking_delta\")]\n157\t    ThinkingDelta { thinking: String },\n158\t}\n159\t```\n160\t\n161\t### 4.2 Client Trait (`crates/llm-compat/src/client.rs`)\n162\t\n163\t```rust\n164\tuse api_types::llm::*;\n165\t\n166\t#[async_trait::async_trait]\n167\tpub trait LlmClient: Send + Sync {\n168\t    /// Send a request and receive a complete response\n169\t    async fn complete(&self, request: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>;\n170\t\n171\t    /// Send a request and receive a stream of events\n172\t    async fn stream(\n173\t        &self,\n174\t        request: LlmRequest,\n175\t    ) -> Result<Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item = Result<StreamEvent, LlmError>> + Send>>, LlmError>;\n176\t}\n177\t```\n178\t\n179\t### 4.3 Provider Adapters (`crates/llm-compat/src/providers/`)\n180\t\n181\t```rust\n182\t/// Anthropic Messages API adapter\n183\tpub struct AnthropicAdapter {\n184\t    http: reqwest::Client,\n185\t    api_key: String,\n186\t    base_url: String,\n187\t}\n188\t\n189\t/// OpenAI Chat Completions API adapter\n190\tpub struct OpenAiAdapter {\n191\t    http: reqwest::Client,\n192\t    api_key: String,\n193\t    base_url: String,\n194\t}\n195\t```\n196\t\n197\tEach adapter implements `LlmClient` by:\n198\t1. Converting `LlmRequest` (Canonical) -> provider wire format\n199\t2. Sending HTTP request\n200\t3. Converting provider response -> `LlmResponse` / `StreamEvent` (Canonical)\n201\t\n202\t### 4.4 Conversion Layer (`crates/llm-compat/src/convert.rs`)\n203\t\n204\tCurrent bidirectional conversion is preserved and extended to triple conversion:\n205\t\n206\t```\n207\tAnthropicRequest ←→ LlmRequest (Canonical) ←→ OpenAiRequest\n208\tAnthropicResponse ←→ LlmResponse (Canonical) ←→ OpenAiResponse\n209\tAnthropicStreamEvent ←→ StreamEvent (Canonical) ←→ OpenAiChunk\n210\t```\n211\t\n212\tExisting functions become internal implementation details of the provider adapters.\n213\tPublic API surface is only `LlmClient` trait + Canonical types.\n214\t\n215\t## 5. Tool Use Mapping\n216\t\n217\t| Canonical | Anthropic Wire | OpenAI Wire |\n218\t|---|---|---|\n219\t| `ContentBlock::ToolUse` | `type: \"tool_use\"` block | `tool_calls[].function` |\n220\t| `ContentBlock::ToolResult` | `type: \"tool_result\"` block | `role: \"tool\"` message |\n221\t| `ToolDefinition` | `tools[].input_schema` | `tools[].function.parameters` |\n222\t| `StopReason::ToolUse` | `stop_reason: \"tool_use\"` | `finish_reason: \"tool_calls\"` |\n223\t\n224\t## 6. Streaming Mapping\n225\t\n226\t| Canonical StreamEvent | Anthropic SSE | OpenAI SSE |\n227\t|---|---|---|\n228\t| `ContentBlockStart` | `content_block_start` | first chunk with role |\n229\t| `ContentBlockDelta::TextDelta` | `content_block_delta` (text) | `choices[].delta.content` |\n230\t| `ContentBlockDelta::InputJsonDelta` | `content_block_delta` (input_json) | `choices[].delta.tool_calls[].function.arguments` |\n231\t| `ContentBlockStop` | `content_block_stop` | (implicit, next block or finish) |\n232\t| `MessageStop` | `message_stop` | `choices[].finish_reason != null` |\n233\t\n234\t## 7. Error Taxonomy\n235\t\n236\t```rust\n237\t#[derive(thiserror::Error, Debug)]\n238\tpub enum LlmError {\n239\t    #[error(\"authentication failed: {0}\")]\n240\t    AuthError(String),\n241\t\n242\t    #[error(\"rate limited, retry after {retry_after_ms:?}ms\")]\n243\t    RateLimited { retry_after_ms: Option<u64> },\n244\t\n245\t    #[error(\"model not found or not available: {0}\")]\n246\t    ModelNotAvailable(String),\n247\t\n248\t    #[error(\"request too large: {0}\")]\n249\t    RequestTooLarge(String),\n250\t\n251\t    #[error(\"provider returned invalid response: {0}\")]\n252\t    InvalidResponse(String),\n253\t\n254\t    #[error(\"stream interrupted: {0}\")]\n255\t    StreamInterrupted(String),\n256\t\n257\t    #[error(\"network error: {0}\")]\n258\t    Network(String),\n259\t\n260\t    #[error(\"timeout after {0:?}\")]\n261\t    Timeout(std::time::Duration),\n262\t\n263\t    #[error(\"provider error ({status}): {message}\")]\n264\t    ProviderError { status: u16, message: String },\n265\t}\n266\t```\n267\t\n268\tPolicy: provider-specific HTTP errors are mapped to `LlmError` variants inside the adapter.\n269\t`app-services` never sees raw HTTP status codes or provider error formats.\n270\t\n271\t## 8. Constants Classification (LLM_COMPAT)\n272\t\n273\t1. `api-types`: Canonical enum variants (`Role`, `StopReason`, `ContentBlock` tag names), `ToolDefinition` schema.\n274\t2. `config`: provider selection key, API key env var names, base URL defaults, model alias table, retry/timeout defaults.\n275\t3. `llm-compat` (crate-local): provider wire format field names, SSE event type strings, HTTP header constants, content-type values.\n276\t\n277\t## 9. Migration Path from Current Code\n278\t\n279\t### Step 1: Introduce Canonical types in `api-types`\n280\tNo breaking changes. New types alongside existing code.\n281\t\n282\t### Step 2: Refactor `llm-compat` conversion\n283\t- Current: `anthropic_request_to_openai_request()` (direct A↔O)\n284\t- Target: `anthropic_request_to_canonical()` + `canonical_to_openai_request()` (via Canonical)\n285\t- Keep old functions as deprecated aliases during migration.\n286\t\n287\t### Step 3: Add `LlmClient` trait and provider adapters\n288\t- `AnthropicAdapter` and `OpenAiAdapter` implement `LlmClient`.\n289\t- Each uses the refactored conversion functions internally.\n290\t\n291\t### Step 4: Add streaming support\n292\t- Implement SSE parsing for both providers.\n293\t- Map provider stream events to `StreamEvent` Canonical type.\n294\t\n295\t### Step 5: Add tool_use support\n296\t- Extend conversion for tool definitions, tool_use blocks, and tool_result blocks.\n297\t- Ensure round-trip correctness for the agent loop.\n298\t\n299\t## 10. Acceptance Criteria\n300\t\n301\t### 10.1 Contract tests\n302\t\n303\t1. `LlmRequest` round-trips through Anthropic wire format without data loss.\n304\t2. `LlmRequest` round-trips through OpenAI wire format without data loss.\n305\t3. `ToolDefinition` schema mapping is bijective between Canonical and both providers.\n306\t4. `StopReason::ToolUse` maps correctly to/from both provider representations.\n307\t5. Streaming events maintain ordering and content integrity through conversion.\n308\t\n309\t### 10.2 Integration tests\n310\t\n311\t1. `AnthropicAdapter::complete()` sends valid Messages API request and parses response.\n312\t2. `OpenAiAdapter::complete()` sends valid Chat Completions request and parses response.\n313\t3. `AnthropicAdapter::stream()` yields correct `StreamEvent` sequence from SSE.\n314\t4. `OpenAiAdapter::stream()` yields correct `StreamEvent` sequence from SSE.\n315\t5. Tool use flow: request with tools -> response with tool_use -> follow-up with tool_result.\n316\t\n317\t### 10.3 Error handling tests\n318\t\n319\t1. 401/403 -> `LlmError::AuthError`.\n320\t2. 429 -> `LlmError::RateLimited` with retry-after extraction.\n321\t3. 413/400 (too large) -> `LlmError::RequestTooLarge`.\n322\t4. Network timeout -> `LlmError::Timeout`.\n323\t5. Malformed response body -> `LlmError::InvalidResponse`.\n324\t\n325\t### 10.4 Agent loop integration\n326\t\n327\t1. `app-services` agent loop can alternate between `complete()` and tool execution using only Canonical types.\n328\t2. Switching provider in `config` requires zero code changes in `app-services`.\n329\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015ehycsq2bes8m9vz6JSD8h","session_id":"33623158-75cc-4f67-b2ef-8a696211d978","uuid":"8437647b-4780-4c19-9e14-b55400765324","timestamp":"2026-04-02T06:37:51.511Z"}
