{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CcZgcWHEJ3tktEAs3ryo7X","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tuse crate::openai_compat::OpenAiCompatAdapter;\n2\tuse async_trait::async_trait;\n3\tuse ccode_ports::provider::{LlmClient, LlmError, LlmRequest, LlmResponse, LlmStream};\n4\t\n5\tpub struct OpenRouterAdapter {\n6\t    adapter: OpenAiCompatAdapter,\n7\t}\n8\t\n9\timpl OpenRouterAdapter {\n10\t    pub fn new(\n11\t        api_key: impl Into<String>,\n12\t        base_url: impl Into<String>,\n13\t        default_model: impl Into<String>,\n14\t        site_url: Option<String>,\n15\t        site_name: Option<String>,\n16\t    ) -> Self {\n17\t        let mut extra_headers = Vec::new();\n18\t        if let Some(url) = site_url {\n19\t            extra_headers.push((\"HTTP-Referer\".into(), url));\n20\t        }\n21\t        if let Some(name) = site_name {\n22\t            extra_headers.push((\"X-Title\".into(), name));\n23\t        }\n24\t        Self {\n25\t            adapter: OpenAiCompatAdapter::new(\n26\t                \"openrouter\",\n27\t                api_key,\n28\t                base_url,\n29\t                default_model,\n30\t                extra_headers,\n31\t            ),\n32\t        }\n33\t    }\n34\t}\n35\t\n36\t#[async_trait]\n37\timpl LlmClient for OpenRouterAdapter {\n38\t    fn name(&self) -> &str {\n39\t        self.adapter.name()\n40\t    }\n41\t\n42\t    fn default_model(&self) -> &str {\n43\t        self.adapter.default_model()\n44\t    }\n45\t\n46\t    async fn health_check(&self) -> Result<(), LlmError> {\n47\t        self.adapter.health_check().await\n48\t    }\n49\t\n50\t    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError> {\n51\t        self.adapter.complete(req).await\n52\t    }\n53\t\n54\t    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError> {\n55\t        self.adapter.stream(req).await\n56\t    }\n57\t}\n58\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015ehycsq2bes8m9vz6JSD8h","session_id":"33623158-75cc-4f67-b2ef-8a696211d978","uuid":"b926e3dd-c5d2-4921-8ad2-03a54b6be6f9","timestamp":"2026-04-02T06:38:22.675Z"}
