{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015ehycsq2bes8m9vz6JSD8h","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Thorough LLM Compatibility Layer Analysis\n\nBased on my detailed exploration of the codebase, here's a comprehensive understanding of the LLM compatibility layer:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Overall Architecture**\n\nThe system implements a **provider-agnostic LLM communication layer** that allows seamless switching between different LLM providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, OpenRouter, Zhipu, LlamaCpp) through a unified interface. The architecture follows these principles:\n\n```\nccode-domain (Message, Role, ToolCall)\n    ↓\nccode-ports (LlmClient trait, canonical request/response types)\n    ↓\nccode-provider (adapters, wire format conversion, compatibility clients)\n    ↓\nUpper layers (app-services, agent loop)\n```\n\n**File Locations:**\n- Contract spec: `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/llm-compat-contract.md`\n- Provider crate: `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/provider/src/`\n- Ports (canonical types): `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/ports/src/provider.rs`\n- Domain (Message types): `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/domain/src/message.rs`\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Canonical Types (Provider-Agnostic)**\n\nThese types are defined in `ccode-ports` and represent the unified interface:\n\n**From `/crates/ports/src/provider.rs`:**\n\n```rust\n// Tool Definition\npub struct ToolDefinition {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub description: String,\n    pub parameters: serde_json::Value,  // JSON Schema\n}\n\n// Request\npub struct LlmRequest {\n    pub messages: Vec<Message>,  // Uses domain Message type\n    pub model: Option<String>,   // None → use provider's default\n    pub max_tokens: Option<u32>,\n    pub temperature: Option<f32>,\n    pub tools: Vec<ToolDefinition>,\n}\n\n// Response\npub struct LlmResponse {\n    pub content: String,\n    pub model: String,\n    pub usage: Option<TokenUsage>,\n}\n\npub struct TokenUsage {\n    pub prompt_tokens: u32,\n    pub completion_tokens: u32,\n    pub total_tokens: u32,\n}\n\n// Streaming\npub enum StreamEvent {\n    Delta { content: String },\n    ToolCallDone { tool_calls: Vec<ToolCall> },\n    Done { usage: Option<TokenUsage> },\n}\n\npub type LlmStream = Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item = Result<StreamEvent, LlmError>> + Send>>;\n\n// Error Taxonomy\npub enum LlmError {\n    AuthError(String),\n    RateLimited { retry_after_ms: Option<u64> },\n    ModelNotAvailable(String),\n    RequestTooLarge(String),\n    InvalidResponse(String),\n    StreamInterrupted(String),\n    Network(String),\n    Timeout(Duration),\n    ProviderError { status: u16, message: String },\n}\n\n// Client Trait\n#[async_trait]\npub trait LlmClient: Send + Sync {\n    fn name(&self) -> &str;\n    fn default_model(&self) -> &str;\n    async fn health_check(&self) -> Result<(), LlmError>;\n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>;\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError>;\n}\n```\n\n**From `/crates/domain/src/message.rs`:**\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub enum Role {\n    System,\n    User,\n    Assistant,\n    Tool,\n}\n\npub struct Message {\n    pub id: MessageId,\n    pub role: Role,\n    pub content: String,\n    pub created_at: u64,        // Unix timestamp (ms)\n    pub tool_calls: Option<Vec<ToolCall>>,\n    pub tool_call_id: Option<String>,\n}\n\npub struct ToolCall {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub name: String,\n    pub arguments: String,      // JSON string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Wire Format Types (Internal to Provider Crate)**\n\nThese live in `/crates/provider/src/compat/` and represent the native format of each provider.\n\n**Anthropic Wire Types** (`compat/request.rs` and `compat/response.rs`):\n\n```rust\n// Request\npub struct AnthropicRequest {\n    pub model: String,\n    pub messages: Vec<Message>,\n    pub max_tokens: Option<u32>,\n    pub temperature: Option<f32>,\n    pub system: Option<SystemContent>,  // Top-level system field (not in messages)\n    pub stream: Option<bool>,\n    pub tools: Vec<AnthropicTool>,\n}\n\npub struct AnthropicTool {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub description: String,\n    pub input_schema: serde_json::Value,  // JSON Schema directly\n}\n\npub enum SystemContent {\n    Text(String),\n    Blocks(Vec<ContentBlock>),\n}\n\npub enum Content {\n    Text(String),\n    Blocks(Vec<ContentBlock>),\n}\n\n// Response\npub struct AnthropicResponse {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub response_type: String,  // \"message\"\n    pub role: String,            // \"assistant\"\n    pub content: Vec<TextBlock>,\n    pub model: String,\n    pub stop_reason: Option<String>,  // \"end_turn\", \"tool_use\", etc.\n    pub usage: Usage,\n}\n\npub struct TextBlock {\n    pub block_type: String,\n    pub text: String,\n}\n\npub struct Usage {\n    pub input_tokens: u32,\n    pub output_tokens: u32,\n}\n\n// Streaming\npub struct AnthropicEvent {\n    pub event_type: String,  // \"message_start\", \"content_block_start\", etc.\n    pub delta: Option<AnthropicEventDelta>,\n    pub message: Option<AnthropicEventMessage>,\n    pub usage: Option<AnthropicDeltaUsage>,\n    pub content_block: Option<AnthropicContentBlock>,\n    pub index: Option<usize>,\n}\n\npub struct AnthropicEventDelta {\n    pub delta_type: String,          // \"text_delta\", \"input_json_delta\"\n    pub text: Option<String>,         // for text_delta\n    pub partial_json: Option<String>, // for input_json_delta (tool input)\n}\n```\n\n**OpenAI Wire Types**:\n\n```rust\n// Request\npub struct OpenAiRequest {\n    pub model: String,\n    pub messages: Vec<OpenAiMessage>,\n    pub max_tokens: Option<u32>,\n    pub temperature: Option<f32>,\n    pub stream: Option<bool>,\n    pub enable_thinking: Option<bool>,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiMessage {\n    pub role: String,\n    pub content: String,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiTool {\n    pub r#type: String,  // \"function\"\n    pub function: OpenAiToolFunction,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiToolFunction {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub description: String,\n    pub parameters: serde_json::Value,  // JSON Schema wrapped in \"parameters\"\n}\n\n// Response\npub struct OpenAiResponse {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub object: String,                   // \"chat.completion\"\n    pub created: u64,\n    pub model: String,\n    pub choices: Vec<OpenAiChoice>,\n    pub usage: Option<OpenAiUsage>,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiChoice {\n    pub index: u32,\n    pub message: OpenAiMessageResponse,\n    pub finish_reason: Option<String>,  // \"stop\", \"tool_calls\", etc.\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiMessageResponse {\n    pub role: String,\n    pub content: Option<String>,\n    pub reasoning_content: Option<String>,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiUsage {\n    pub prompt_tokens: u32,\n    pub completion_tokens: u32,\n    pub total_tokens: u32,\n}\n\n// Streaming\npub struct StreamChunk {\n    pub choices: Vec<StreamChoice>,\n    pub usage: Option<UsageStats>,\n}\n\npub struct StreamChoice {\n    pub delta: DeltaContent,\n    pub finish_reason: Option<String>,\n}\n\npub struct DeltaContent {\n    pub content: Option<String>,\n    pub tool_calls: Option<Vec<StreamToolCallDelta>>,\n}\n\npub struct StreamToolCallDelta {\n    pub index: usize,\n    pub id: Option<String>,\n    pub function: Option<StreamToolCallFunctionDelta>,\n}\n\npub struct StreamToolCallFunctionDelta {\n    pub name: Option<String>,\n    pub arguments: Option<String>,  // Streamed JSON\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Wire Format Conversion Code**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/compat/convert.rs`\n\nThis file contains bidirectional conversion functions between wire formats:\n\n```rust\n// Request conversion\npub fn anthropic_request_to_openai_request(\n    anthropic_req: AnthropicRequest,\n    options: AnthropicToOpenAiOptions,\n) -> OpenAiRequest\n\npub fn openai_request_to_anthropic_request(openai_req: OpenAiRequest) -> AnthropicRequest\n\n// Response conversion\npub fn openai_response_to_anthropic_response(\n    openai_resp: OpenAiResponse,\n    original_model: impl Into<String>,\n) -> AnthropicResponse\n\npub fn anthropic_response_to_openai_response(\n    anthropic_resp: AnthropicResponse,\n    target_model: impl Into<String>,\n) -> OpenAiResponse\n\n// Tool definition conversion\npub fn anthropic_tool_to_openai_function(\n    anthropic_tool: serde_json::Value,\n) -> Result<serde_json::Value, String>\n\npub fn openai_function_to_anthropic_tool(\n    openai_function: serde_json::Value,\n) -> Result<serde_json::Value, String>\n\n// Stop reason mapping\nfn map_stop_reason_openai_to_anthropic(reason: &str) -> String\nfn map_stop_reason_anthropic_to_openai(reason: &str) -> String\n```\n\n**Key Conversion Rules:**\n\n1. **System Messages:**\n   - Anthropic: Top-level `system` field (not in messages array)\n   - OpenAI: System message in messages array with role=\"system\"\n   - Conversion: Extract or insert as needed\n\n2. **Tool Use:**\n   - Anthropic: `input_schema` field directly\n   - OpenAI: `parameters` field (wrapped)\n   - Conversion: `anthropic_tool_to_openai_function()` renames `input_schema` → `parameters`\n\n3. **Stop Reasons:**\n   - Anthropic: `\"tool_use\"`\n   - OpenAI: `\"tool_calls\"`\n   - Other values pass through unchanged\n\n4. **Content Block Representation:**\n   - Anthropic: Mixed (text string or block array)\n   - OpenAI: Flat string\n   - Conversion: Flattened during conversion, text blocks joined with newlines\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Anthropic Adapter Implementation**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/anthropic_compat/client.rs`\n\nThe `AnthropicCompatClient` implements HTTP communication with Anthropic's Messages API:\n\n```rust\npub struct AnthropicCompatClient {\n    client: reqwest::Client,\n    pub api_key: String,\n    pub base_url: String,\n    pub default_model: String,\n}\n\nimpl AnthropicCompatClient {\n    // Headers: x-api-key (not Bearer), anthropic-version: 2023-06-01\n    \n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError>\n    \n    // Internal helper to convert canonical requests\n    fn split_system(&self, req: &LlmRequest) -> (Option<String>, Vec<AnthropicMessage>)\n    fn build_body(&self, req: &LlmRequest, stream: bool) -> AnthropicRequest\n}\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n\n1. **System Messages:** Extracted from `LlmRequest.messages`, merged into single top-level `system` field\n2. **Tool Results:** Consecutive `Role::Tool` messages are merged into a single user message (Anthropic prohibits consecutive same role)\n3. **Tool Use Blocks:** Assistant messages with tool_calls generate `tool_use` content blocks\n4. **Error Mapping:**\n   - 401/403 → `AuthError`\n   - 429 → `RateLimited` (extracts `retry-after` header)\n   - 413/400 \"too large\" → `RequestTooLarge`\n   - 404 → `ModelNotAvailable`\n   - Timeout → `Timeout(30s)`\n\n5. **Streaming:** SSE parsing with state machine for tool_use accumulation\n   - Events: `message_start`, `content_block_start`, `content_block_delta`, `content_block_stop`, `message_delta`, `message_stop`\n   - Tool inputs streamed via `input_json_delta` and accumulated\n\n**From `/crates/provider/src/anthropic_compat/types.rs`:**\n\n```rust\n// Anthropic-specific streaming types\npub struct AnthropicEvent {\n    pub event_type: String,\n    pub delta: Option<AnthropicEventDelta>,\n    pub message: Option<AnthropicEventMessage>,\n    pub usage: Option<AnthropicDeltaUsage>,\n    pub content_block: Option<AnthropicContentBlock>,\n    pub index: Option<usize>,\n}\n\npub struct AnthropicContentBlock {\n    pub block_type: String,           // \"text\", \"tool_use\"\n    pub id: Option<String>,            // tool_use id\n    pub name: Option<String>,          // tool_use name\n}\n\npub struct AnthropicEventDelta {\n    pub delta_type: String,            // \"text_delta\", \"input_json_delta\"\n    pub text: Option<String>,\n    pub partial_json: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n\n**Conversion Function (Internal):**\n\n```rust\nfn convert_anthropic_event_to_events(\n    event: AnthropicEvent,\n    state: &mut AnthropicStreamState,\n) -> (Vec<StreamEvent>, bool)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **OpenAI-Compatible Adapter Implementation**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/openai_compat/client.rs`\n\nThe `OpenAiCompatClient` implements HTTP communication for OpenAI-compatible APIs:\n\n```rust\npub struct OpenAiCompatClient {\n    client: reqwest::Client,\n    pub api_key: String,\n    pub base_url: String,\n    pub default_model: String,\n    extra_headers: Vec<(String, String)>,  // For custom providers like OpenRouter\n}\n\nimpl OpenAiCompatClient {\n    // Headers: Bearer auth (not x-api-key)\n    \n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError>\n    \n    fn build_body(&self, req: &LlmRequest, stream: bool) -> ChatRequest\n    fn add_headers(&self, builder: RequestBuilder) -> RequestBuilder\n}\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n\n1. **System Messages:** Remain in messages array (role=\"system\")\n2. **Tool Role:** Uses OpenAI's special \"tool\" role with `tool_call_id` field\n3. **Tool Calls:** Streamed in `delta.tool_calls` with incremental accumulation\n4. **Error Mapping:** Same as Anthropic\n5. **Streaming:** SSE with `[DONE]` sentinel\n   - Tool calls accumulated in buffer, flushed on finish_reason\n   - Text and tool_calls can be interleaved\n\n**From `/crates/provider/src/openai_compat/types.rs`:**\n\n```rust\npub struct ChatMessage {\n    pub role: String,\n    pub content: Option<String>,       // None for pure tool calls\n    pub tool_calls: Option<Vec<OpenAiToolCall>>,\n    pub tool_call_id: Option<String>,  // For \"tool\" role messages\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiToolCall {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub r#type: String,  // \"function\"\n    pub function: OpenAiToolCallFunction,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiToolCallFunction {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub arguments: String,  // JSON string\n}\n```\n\n**Conversion Function (Internal):**\n\n```rust\nfn convert_chunk_to_events(\n    chunk: StreamChunk,\n    tool_call_buf: &mut ToolCallBuffer,\n) -> (Vec<StreamEvent>, bool)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Adapter Wiring**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/anthropic/adapter.rs` and similar\n\n```rust\npub struct AnthropicAdapter {\n    client: AnthropicCompatClient,\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\nimpl LlmClient for AnthropicAdapter {\n    fn name(&self) -> &str { \"anthropic\" }\n    fn default_model(&self) -> &str { &self.client.default_model }\n    async fn health_check(&self) -> Result<(), LlmError> { ... }\n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError> { ... }\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError> { ... }\n}\n```\n\n**OpenRouter and other adapters** wrap the `OpenAiCompatClient`:\n\n```rust\npub struct OpenRouterAdapter {\n    adapter: OpenAiCompatAdapter,  // Uses OpenAI wire format\n}\n\n// Extra headers: HTTP-Referer, X-Title\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Factory & Routing**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/factory.rs` and `/crates/provider/src/router.rs`\n\n```rust\npub fn build(name: &str, config: &Config) -> Result<Arc<dyn LlmClient>, FactoryError>\n// Builds single provider: \"anthropic\", \"openrouter\", \"zhipu\", \"llamacpp\"\n\npub fn build_default(config: &Config) -> Result<Arc<dyn LlmClient>, FactoryError>\n// Builds router or single provider based on config.routing.strategy\n\npub enum RoutingStrategy {\n    Manual,        // Single provider (config.routing.default_provider)\n    Failover,      // Try providers in order\n    RoundRobin,    // Distribute requests across all\n}\n\npub struct ProviderRouter {\n    providers: Vec<Arc<dyn LlmClient>>,\n    strategy: RoutingStrategy,\n    rr_cursor: AtomicUsize,\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\nimpl LlmClient for ProviderRouter {\n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError> {\n        // On Failover: try each provider, advance on error\n        // Otherwise: pick based on strategy (Manual/RoundRobin)\n    }\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError> { ... }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Existing Tests**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/tests/compat_conversion.rs`\n\nTests verify bidirectional conversion correctness:\n\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn anthropic_request_converts_to_openai_request_with_system_and_thinking_option()\n// Validates system message extraction, message ordering\n\n#[test]\nfn openai_request_converts_back_to_anthropic_request()\n// Validates system message reinsertion, message filtering\n\n#[test]\nfn openai_response_converts_to_anthropic_response()\n// Validates token usage mapping, content preservation\n\n#[test]\nfn anthropic_response_converts_back_to_openai_response()\n// Validates round-trip response integrity\n\n#[test]\nfn stop_reason_tool_use_maps_between_wire_formats()\n// Validates \"tool_calls\" ↔ \"tool_use\" mapping\n\n#[test]\nfn tool_definition_schema_roundtrips_between_anthropic_and_openai()\n// Validates input_schema ↔ parameters mapping\n```\n\n**In-Module Tests:**\n\n- `anthropic_compat/client.rs`: Error mapping, streaming event order preservation\n- `openai_compat/client.rs`: Error mapping, streaming chunk with interleaved text and tool calls\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Key Insights**\n\n1. **Two-Level Architecture:**\n   - Upper level: `LlmClient` trait + canonical types (provider-agnostic)\n   - Lower level: Wire format types + conversion functions (provider-specific, internal)\n\n2. **No Provider Leakage:**\n   - `ccode-ports` has zero provider knowledge\n   - `ccode-domain` has zero provider knowledge\n   - All wire types are `pub(crate)` in provider crate (except in tests)\n\n3. **Tool Use Handling:**\n   - Anthropic: `content_block` array with `tool_use` blocks\n   - OpenAI: `tool_calls` array in message\n   - Streaming: Input accumulated character-by-character (Anthropic `input_json_delta`, OpenAI `function.arguments`)\n\n4. **System Message Handling:**\n   - Anthropic: Top-level field, separate from messages\n   - OpenAI: First message in array with role=\"system\"\n   - Conversion: Extract/insert as needed\n\n5. **Streaming State Machine:**\n   - Both use SSE (Server-Sent Events) over HTTP\n   - Both accumulate tool inputs incrementally\n   - Anthropic: `message_stop` final event\n   - OpenAI: `[DONE]` sentinel in data field\n\n6. **Error Semantics:**\n   - Canonical `LlmError` enum with variants for all provider error classes\n   - HTTP status codes mapped to semantic errors (e.g., 429 → RateLimited with retry-after)\n   - Context-aware (e.g., 400 \"too large\" → RequestTooLarge)\n\n7. **Configuration-Driven Provider Selection:**\n   - Factory builds adapters from config\n   - Router implements failover and round-robin\n   - Zero code changes needed to switch providers (upper layers)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Dependency Graph**\n\n```\ndomain/message.rs (Message, Role, ToolCall)\n    ↓\nports/provider.rs (LlmClient trait, LlmRequest, LlmResponse, StreamEvent, LlmError)\n    ↓\nprovider/compat/request.rs (AnthropicRequest, OpenAiRequest — internal)\nprovider/compat/response.rs (AnthropicResponse, OpenAiResponse — internal)\nprovider/compat/convert.rs (conversion functions — internal)\n    ↓\nprovider/anthropic_compat/client.rs (AnthropicCompatClient)\nprovider/openai_compat/client.rs (OpenAiCompatClient)\n    ↓\nprovider/anthropic/adapter.rs (AnthropicAdapter : LlmClient)\nprovider/openai_compat/mod.rs (OpenAiCompatAdapter : LlmClient)\nprovider/openrouter/adapter.rs (OpenRouterAdapter : LlmClient)\n    ↓\nprovider/factory.rs (build adapters from config)\nprovider/router.rs (ProviderRouter : LlmClient — failover/round-robin)\n    ↓\napp-services (agent loop — uses LlmClient trait only)\n```\n\nThis architecture ensures **complete provider isolation** while maintaining **unified semantics** across all LLM interactions."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"33623158-75cc-4f67-b2ef-8a696211d978","uuid":"8ea2e465-c9ec-442c-9642-290e33ded205","timestamp":"2026-04-02T06:39:11.899Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode to understand the LLM compatibility layer. I need to understand:\n\n1. The structure of the platform crate (crates/platform/src/)\n2. Any existing LLM adapter code (Anthropic, OpenAI adapters)\n3. The llm-compat-contract.md file if it exists\n4. Existing test structure\n5. The Cargo.toml files to understand dependencies\n\nPlease read key files and give me a thorough understanding of:\n- What types exist (LlmRequest, ToolDefinition, StopReason, StreamEvent, LlmError, etc.)\n- How AnthropicAdapter and OpenAiAdapter are implemented\n- What wire format conversion code exists\n- Any existing tests\n\nBe thorough - read the actual source files.","agentId":"a23b76deae4bff1d6","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Thorough LLM Compatibility Layer Analysis\n\nBased on my detailed exploration of the codebase, here's a comprehensive understanding of the LLM compatibility layer:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Overall Architecture**\n\nThe system implements a **provider-agnostic LLM communication layer** that allows seamless switching between different LLM providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, OpenRouter, Zhipu, LlamaCpp) through a unified interface. The architecture follows these principles:\n\n```\nccode-domain (Message, Role, ToolCall)\n    ↓\nccode-ports (LlmClient trait, canonical request/response types)\n    ↓\nccode-provider (adapters, wire format conversion, compatibility clients)\n    ↓\nUpper layers (app-services, agent loop)\n```\n\n**File Locations:**\n- Contract spec: `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/llm-compat-contract.md`\n- Provider crate: `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/provider/src/`\n- Ports (canonical types): `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/ports/src/provider.rs`\n- Domain (Message types): `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/crates/domain/src/message.rs`\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Canonical Types (Provider-Agnostic)**\n\nThese types are defined in `ccode-ports` and represent the unified interface:\n\n**From `/crates/ports/src/provider.rs`:**\n\n```rust\n// Tool Definition\npub struct ToolDefinition {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub description: String,\n    pub parameters: serde_json::Value,  // JSON Schema\n}\n\n// Request\npub struct LlmRequest {\n    pub messages: Vec<Message>,  // Uses domain Message type\n    pub model: Option<String>,   // None → use provider's default\n    pub max_tokens: Option<u32>,\n    pub temperature: Option<f32>,\n    pub tools: Vec<ToolDefinition>,\n}\n\n// Response\npub struct LlmResponse {\n    pub content: String,\n    pub model: String,\n    pub usage: Option<TokenUsage>,\n}\n\npub struct TokenUsage {\n    pub prompt_tokens: u32,\n    pub completion_tokens: u32,\n    pub total_tokens: u32,\n}\n\n// Streaming\npub enum StreamEvent {\n    Delta { content: String },\n    ToolCallDone { tool_calls: Vec<ToolCall> },\n    Done { usage: Option<TokenUsage> },\n}\n\npub type LlmStream = Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item = Result<StreamEvent, LlmError>> + Send>>;\n\n// Error Taxonomy\npub enum LlmError {\n    AuthError(String),\n    RateLimited { retry_after_ms: Option<u64> },\n    ModelNotAvailable(String),\n    RequestTooLarge(String),\n    InvalidResponse(String),\n    StreamInterrupted(String),\n    Network(String),\n    Timeout(Duration),\n    ProviderError { status: u16, message: String },\n}\n\n// Client Trait\n#[async_trait]\npub trait LlmClient: Send + Sync {\n    fn name(&self) -> &str;\n    fn default_model(&self) -> &str;\n    async fn health_check(&self) -> Result<(), LlmError>;\n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>;\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError>;\n}\n```\n\n**From `/crates/domain/src/message.rs`:**\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub enum Role {\n    System,\n    User,\n    Assistant,\n    Tool,\n}\n\npub struct Message {\n    pub id: MessageId,\n    pub role: Role,\n    pub content: String,\n    pub created_at: u64,        // Unix timestamp (ms)\n    pub tool_calls: Option<Vec<ToolCall>>,\n    pub tool_call_id: Option<String>,\n}\n\npub struct ToolCall {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub name: String,\n    pub arguments: String,      // JSON string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Wire Format Types (Internal to Provider Crate)**\n\nThese live in `/crates/provider/src/compat/` and represent the native format of each provider.\n\n**Anthropic Wire Types** (`compat/request.rs` and `compat/response.rs`):\n\n```rust\n// Request\npub struct AnthropicRequest {\n    pub model: String,\n    pub messages: Vec<Message>,\n    pub max_tokens: Option<u32>,\n    pub temperature: Option<f32>,\n    pub system: Option<SystemContent>,  // Top-level system field (not in messages)\n    pub stream: Option<bool>,\n    pub tools: Vec<AnthropicTool>,\n}\n\npub struct AnthropicTool {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub description: String,\n    pub input_schema: serde_json::Value,  // JSON Schema directly\n}\n\npub enum SystemContent {\n    Text(String),\n    Blocks(Vec<ContentBlock>),\n}\n\npub enum Content {\n    Text(String),\n    Blocks(Vec<ContentBlock>),\n}\n\n// Response\npub struct AnthropicResponse {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub response_type: String,  // \"message\"\n    pub role: String,            // \"assistant\"\n    pub content: Vec<TextBlock>,\n    pub model: String,\n    pub stop_reason: Option<String>,  // \"end_turn\", \"tool_use\", etc.\n    pub usage: Usage,\n}\n\npub struct TextBlock {\n    pub block_type: String,\n    pub text: String,\n}\n\npub struct Usage {\n    pub input_tokens: u32,\n    pub output_tokens: u32,\n}\n\n// Streaming\npub struct AnthropicEvent {\n    pub event_type: String,  // \"message_start\", \"content_block_start\", etc.\n    pub delta: Option<AnthropicEventDelta>,\n    pub message: Option<AnthropicEventMessage>,\n    pub usage: Option<AnthropicDeltaUsage>,\n    pub content_block: Option<AnthropicContentBlock>,\n    pub index: Option<usize>,\n}\n\npub struct AnthropicEventDelta {\n    pub delta_type: String,          // \"text_delta\", \"input_json_delta\"\n    pub text: Option<String>,         // for text_delta\n    pub partial_json: Option<String>, // for input_json_delta (tool input)\n}\n```\n\n**OpenAI Wire Types**:\n\n```rust\n// Request\npub struct OpenAiRequest {\n    pub model: String,\n    pub messages: Vec<OpenAiMessage>,\n    pub max_tokens: Option<u32>,\n    pub temperature: Option<f32>,\n    pub stream: Option<bool>,\n    pub enable_thinking: Option<bool>,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiMessage {\n    pub role: String,\n    pub content: String,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiTool {\n    pub r#type: String,  // \"function\"\n    pub function: OpenAiToolFunction,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiToolFunction {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub description: String,\n    pub parameters: serde_json::Value,  // JSON Schema wrapped in \"parameters\"\n}\n\n// Response\npub struct OpenAiResponse {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub object: String,                   // \"chat.completion\"\n    pub created: u64,\n    pub model: String,\n    pub choices: Vec<OpenAiChoice>,\n    pub usage: Option<OpenAiUsage>,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiChoice {\n    pub index: u32,\n    pub message: OpenAiMessageResponse,\n    pub finish_reason: Option<String>,  // \"stop\", \"tool_calls\", etc.\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiMessageResponse {\n    pub role: String,\n    pub content: Option<String>,\n    pub reasoning_content: Option<String>,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiUsage {\n    pub prompt_tokens: u32,\n    pub completion_tokens: u32,\n    pub total_tokens: u32,\n}\n\n// Streaming\npub struct StreamChunk {\n    pub choices: Vec<StreamChoice>,\n    pub usage: Option<UsageStats>,\n}\n\npub struct StreamChoice {\n    pub delta: DeltaContent,\n    pub finish_reason: Option<String>,\n}\n\npub struct DeltaContent {\n    pub content: Option<String>,\n    pub tool_calls: Option<Vec<StreamToolCallDelta>>,\n}\n\npub struct StreamToolCallDelta {\n    pub index: usize,\n    pub id: Option<String>,\n    pub function: Option<StreamToolCallFunctionDelta>,\n}\n\npub struct StreamToolCallFunctionDelta {\n    pub name: Option<String>,\n    pub arguments: Option<String>,  // Streamed JSON\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Wire Format Conversion Code**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/compat/convert.rs`\n\nThis file contains bidirectional conversion functions between wire formats:\n\n```rust\n// Request conversion\npub fn anthropic_request_to_openai_request(\n    anthropic_req: AnthropicRequest,\n    options: AnthropicToOpenAiOptions,\n) -> OpenAiRequest\n\npub fn openai_request_to_anthropic_request(openai_req: OpenAiRequest) -> AnthropicRequest\n\n// Response conversion\npub fn openai_response_to_anthropic_response(\n    openai_resp: OpenAiResponse,\n    original_model: impl Into<String>,\n) -> AnthropicResponse\n\npub fn anthropic_response_to_openai_response(\n    anthropic_resp: AnthropicResponse,\n    target_model: impl Into<String>,\n) -> OpenAiResponse\n\n// Tool definition conversion\npub fn anthropic_tool_to_openai_function(\n    anthropic_tool: serde_json::Value,\n) -> Result<serde_json::Value, String>\n\npub fn openai_function_to_anthropic_tool(\n    openai_function: serde_json::Value,\n) -> Result<serde_json::Value, String>\n\n// Stop reason mapping\nfn map_stop_reason_openai_to_anthropic(reason: &str) -> String\nfn map_stop_reason_anthropic_to_openai(reason: &str) -> String\n```\n\n**Key Conversion Rules:**\n\n1. **System Messages:**\n   - Anthropic: Top-level `system` field (not in messages array)\n   - OpenAI: System message in messages array with role=\"system\"\n   - Conversion: Extract or insert as needed\n\n2. **Tool Use:**\n   - Anthropic: `input_schema` field directly\n   - OpenAI: `parameters` field (wrapped)\n   - Conversion: `anthropic_tool_to_openai_function()` renames `input_schema` → `parameters`\n\n3. **Stop Reasons:**\n   - Anthropic: `\"tool_use\"`\n   - OpenAI: `\"tool_calls\"`\n   - Other values pass through unchanged\n\n4. **Content Block Representation:**\n   - Anthropic: Mixed (text string or block array)\n   - OpenAI: Flat string\n   - Conversion: Flattened during conversion, text blocks joined with newlines\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Anthropic Adapter Implementation**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/anthropic_compat/client.rs`\n\nThe `AnthropicCompatClient` implements HTTP communication with Anthropic's Messages API:\n\n```rust\npub struct AnthropicCompatClient {\n    client: reqwest::Client,\n    pub api_key: String,\n    pub base_url: String,\n    pub default_model: String,\n}\n\nimpl AnthropicCompatClient {\n    // Headers: x-api-key (not Bearer), anthropic-version: 2023-06-01\n    \n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError>\n    \n    // Internal helper to convert canonical requests\n    fn split_system(&self, req: &LlmRequest) -> (Option<String>, Vec<AnthropicMessage>)\n    fn build_body(&self, req: &LlmRequest, stream: bool) -> AnthropicRequest\n}\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n\n1. **System Messages:** Extracted from `LlmRequest.messages`, merged into single top-level `system` field\n2. **Tool Results:** Consecutive `Role::Tool` messages are merged into a single user message (Anthropic prohibits consecutive same role)\n3. **Tool Use Blocks:** Assistant messages with tool_calls generate `tool_use` content blocks\n4. **Error Mapping:**\n   - 401/403 → `AuthError`\n   - 429 → `RateLimited` (extracts `retry-after` header)\n   - 413/400 \"too large\" → `RequestTooLarge`\n   - 404 → `ModelNotAvailable`\n   - Timeout → `Timeout(30s)`\n\n5. **Streaming:** SSE parsing with state machine for tool_use accumulation\n   - Events: `message_start`, `content_block_start`, `content_block_delta`, `content_block_stop`, `message_delta`, `message_stop`\n   - Tool inputs streamed via `input_json_delta` and accumulated\n\n**From `/crates/provider/src/anthropic_compat/types.rs`:**\n\n```rust\n// Anthropic-specific streaming types\npub struct AnthropicEvent {\n    pub event_type: String,\n    pub delta: Option<AnthropicEventDelta>,\n    pub message: Option<AnthropicEventMessage>,\n    pub usage: Option<AnthropicDeltaUsage>,\n    pub content_block: Option<AnthropicContentBlock>,\n    pub index: Option<usize>,\n}\n\npub struct AnthropicContentBlock {\n    pub block_type: String,           // \"text\", \"tool_use\"\n    pub id: Option<String>,            // tool_use id\n    pub name: Option<String>,          // tool_use name\n}\n\npub struct AnthropicEventDelta {\n    pub delta_type: String,            // \"text_delta\", \"input_json_delta\"\n    pub text: Option<String>,\n    pub partial_json: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n\n**Conversion Function (Internal):**\n\n```rust\nfn convert_anthropic_event_to_events(\n    event: AnthropicEvent,\n    state: &mut AnthropicStreamState,\n) -> (Vec<StreamEvent>, bool)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **OpenAI-Compatible Adapter Implementation**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/openai_compat/client.rs`\n\nThe `OpenAiCompatClient` implements HTTP communication for OpenAI-compatible APIs:\n\n```rust\npub struct OpenAiCompatClient {\n    client: reqwest::Client,\n    pub api_key: String,\n    pub base_url: String,\n    pub default_model: String,\n    extra_headers: Vec<(String, String)>,  // For custom providers like OpenRouter\n}\n\nimpl OpenAiCompatClient {\n    // Headers: Bearer auth (not x-api-key)\n    \n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError>\n    \n    fn build_body(&self, req: &LlmRequest, stream: bool) -> ChatRequest\n    fn add_headers(&self, builder: RequestBuilder) -> RequestBuilder\n}\n```\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n\n1. **System Messages:** Remain in messages array (role=\"system\")\n2. **Tool Role:** Uses OpenAI's special \"tool\" role with `tool_call_id` field\n3. **Tool Calls:** Streamed in `delta.tool_calls` with incremental accumulation\n4. **Error Mapping:** Same as Anthropic\n5. **Streaming:** SSE with `[DONE]` sentinel\n   - Tool calls accumulated in buffer, flushed on finish_reason\n   - Text and tool_calls can be interleaved\n\n**From `/crates/provider/src/openai_compat/types.rs`:**\n\n```rust\npub struct ChatMessage {\n    pub role: String,\n    pub content: Option<String>,       // None for pure tool calls\n    pub tool_calls: Option<Vec<OpenAiToolCall>>,\n    pub tool_call_id: Option<String>,  // For \"tool\" role messages\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiToolCall {\n    pub id: String,\n    pub r#type: String,  // \"function\"\n    pub function: OpenAiToolCallFunction,\n}\n\npub struct OpenAiToolCallFunction {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub arguments: String,  // JSON string\n}\n```\n\n**Conversion Function (Internal):**\n\n```rust\nfn convert_chunk_to_events(\n    chunk: StreamChunk,\n    tool_call_buf: &mut ToolCallBuffer,\n) -> (Vec<StreamEvent>, bool)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Adapter Wiring**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/anthropic/adapter.rs` and similar\n\n```rust\npub struct AnthropicAdapter {\n    client: AnthropicCompatClient,\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\nimpl LlmClient for AnthropicAdapter {\n    fn name(&self) -> &str { \"anthropic\" }\n    fn default_model(&self) -> &str { &self.client.default_model }\n    async fn health_check(&self) -> Result<(), LlmError> { ... }\n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError> { ... }\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError> { ... }\n}\n```\n\n**OpenRouter and other adapters** wrap the `OpenAiCompatClient`:\n\n```rust\npub struct OpenRouterAdapter {\n    adapter: OpenAiCompatAdapter,  // Uses OpenAI wire format\n}\n\n// Extra headers: HTTP-Referer, X-Title\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Factory & Routing**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/src/factory.rs` and `/crates/provider/src/router.rs`\n\n```rust\npub fn build(name: &str, config: &Config) -> Result<Arc<dyn LlmClient>, FactoryError>\n// Builds single provider: \"anthropic\", \"openrouter\", \"zhipu\", \"llamacpp\"\n\npub fn build_default(config: &Config) -> Result<Arc<dyn LlmClient>, FactoryError>\n// Builds router or single provider based on config.routing.strategy\n\npub enum RoutingStrategy {\n    Manual,        // Single provider (config.routing.default_provider)\n    Failover,      // Try providers in order\n    RoundRobin,    // Distribute requests across all\n}\n\npub struct ProviderRouter {\n    providers: Vec<Arc<dyn LlmClient>>,\n    strategy: RoutingStrategy,\n    rr_cursor: AtomicUsize,\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\nimpl LlmClient for ProviderRouter {\n    async fn complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError> {\n        // On Failover: try each provider, advance on error\n        // Otherwise: pick based on strategy (Manual/RoundRobin)\n    }\n    async fn stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmStream, LlmError> { ... }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Existing Tests**\n\n**Location:** `/crates/provider/tests/compat_conversion.rs`\n\nTests verify bidirectional conversion correctness:\n\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn anthropic_request_converts_to_openai_request_with_system_and_thinking_option()\n// Validates system message extraction, message ordering\n\n#[test]\nfn openai_request_converts_back_to_anthropic_request()\n// Validates system message reinsertion, message filtering\n\n#[test]\nfn openai_response_converts_to_anthropic_response()\n// Validates token usage mapping, content preservation\n\n#[test]\nfn anthropic_response_converts_back_to_openai_response()\n// Validates round-trip response integrity\n\n#[test]\nfn stop_reason_tool_use_maps_between_wire_formats()\n// Validates \"tool_calls\" ↔ \"tool_use\" mapping\n\n#[test]\nfn tool_definition_schema_roundtrips_between_anthropic_and_openai()\n// Validates input_schema ↔ parameters mapping\n```\n\n**In-Module Tests:**\n\n- `anthropic_compat/client.rs`: Error mapping, streaming event order preservation\n- `openai_compat/client.rs`: Error mapping, streaming chunk with interleaved text and tool calls\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Key Insights**\n\n1. **Two-Level Architecture:**\n   - Upper level: `LlmClient` trait + canonical types (provider-agnostic)\n   - Lower level: Wire format types + conversion functions (provider-specific, internal)\n\n2. **No Provider Leakage:**\n   - `ccode-ports` has zero provider knowledge\n   - `ccode-domain` has zero provider knowledge\n   - All wire types are `pub(crate)` in provider crate (except in tests)\n\n3. **Tool Use Handling:**\n   - Anthropic: `content_block` array with `tool_use` blocks\n   - OpenAI: `tool_calls` array in message\n   - Streaming: Input accumulated character-by-character (Anthropic `input_json_delta`, OpenAI `function.arguments`)\n\n4. **System Message Handling:**\n   - Anthropic: Top-level field, separate from messages\n   - OpenAI: First message in array with role=\"system\"\n   - Conversion: Extract/insert as needed\n\n5. **Streaming State Machine:**\n   - Both use SSE (Server-Sent Events) over HTTP\n   - Both accumulate tool inputs incrementally\n   - Anthropic: `message_stop` final event\n   - OpenAI: `[DONE]` sentinel in data field\n\n6. **Error Semantics:**\n   - Canonical `LlmError` enum with variants for all provider error classes\n   - HTTP status codes mapped to semantic errors (e.g., 429 → RateLimited with retry-after)\n   - Context-aware (e.g., 400 \"too large\" → RequestTooLarge)\n\n7. **Configuration-Driven Provider Selection:**\n   - Factory builds adapters from config\n   - Router implements failover and round-robin\n   - Zero code changes needed to switch providers (upper layers)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Dependency Graph**\n\n```\ndomain/message.rs (Message, Role, ToolCall)\n    ↓\nports/provider.rs (LlmClient trait, LlmRequest, LlmResponse, StreamEvent, LlmError)\n    ↓\nprovider/compat/request.rs (AnthropicRequest, OpenAiRequest — internal)\nprovider/compat/response.rs (AnthropicResponse, OpenAiResponse — internal)\nprovider/compat/convert.rs (conversion functions — internal)\n    ↓\nprovider/anthropic_compat/client.rs (AnthropicCompatClient)\nprovider/openai_compat/client.rs (OpenAiCompatClient)\n    ↓\nprovider/anthropic/adapter.rs (AnthropicAdapter : LlmClient)\nprovider/openai_compat/mod.rs (OpenAiCompatAdapter : LlmClient)\nprovider/openrouter/adapter.rs (OpenRouterAdapter : LlmClient)\n    ↓\nprovider/factory.rs (build adapters from config)\nprovider/router.rs (ProviderRouter : LlmClient — failover/round-robin)\n    ↓\napp-services (agent loop — uses LlmClient trait only)\n```\n\nThis architecture ensures **complete provider isolation** while maintaining **unified semantics** across all LLM interactions."}],"totalDurationMs":94545,"totalTokens":76288,"totalToolUseCount":29,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2841,"cache_read_input_tokens":67385,"output_tokens":6060,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2841},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
