{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GRp3dpEC1Ez7NAdSAEn1x8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JYkUi1Kki3GaiN3S5wwHMq","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git add crates/provider/Cargo.toml crates/provider/src/anthropic_compat/client.rs crates/provider/src/anthropic/adapter.rs crates/provider/tests/contract.rs crates/provider/tests/integration.rs crates/provider/tests/agent_loop.rs Cargo.lock && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfeat: US-036 - LLM compat acceptance test suite\n\nAdds comprehensive acceptance tests covering all criteria from\nllm-compat-contract.md §10.1–§10.4:\n\nContract tests (contract.rs): AC1/AC2 serialisation round-trips for\nAnthropic and OpenAI wire formats, AC3 bijective ToolDefinition schema\nmapping, AC4 bidirectional StopReason::ToolUse translation.\n\nIntegration tests (integration.rs): AC1/AC2 wire format capture via\nwiremock, AC6/AC7 complete(), AC8/AC9 stream(), AC10 tool-use flow\n(request → tool_use → tool_result → final answer), AC11–AC15 HTTP\nerror code mapping (401/403 AuthError, 429 RateLimited, 413/400\nRequestTooLarge, timeout Timeout, malformed body InvalidResponse),\nAC17 provider switching without code changes.\n\nAgent-loop tests (agent_loop.rs): AC5 streaming event ordering and\ncontent integrity via StepClient mock, AC16 agent loop using only\ncanonical types with two-iteration tool-execution cycle.\n\nAdds wiremock dev-dependency and AnthropicAdapter/AnthropicCompatClient\ntest constructors for custom reqwest::Client injection (timeout tests).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit US-036 acceptance tests","timeout":30000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":368,"cache_read_input_tokens":164267,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":368,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens"